<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/602: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-05T00:00:00-05:00">November 5,
                                    1941—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1096. Department’s 941, October 13, 10 p.m. and your 1556, October 22, 3
                                p.m.<note n="75" xml:id="d538fn1">Latter not printed.</note>
                            Contract between Pan American Airways and subsidiary of Reconstruction
                            Finance Corporation to provide substitute service for Lati has been
                            signed.</p>
                        <p>Copy is being sent you air mail. Please inform Harding.<note n="76" xml:id="d538fn2">William Barclay Harding, vice president of the
                                Defense Supplies Corporation.</note></p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>